Trim the @green beans{80%grams}, then cut into thirds. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce the heat to medium, then add the garlic and @ginger puree{15%grams} and stir-fry, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @sliced spring greens{150%grams} along with the @water{1%tbsp} for the greens, cover with a #tight-fitting lid{} and cook until wilted, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine the @hoisin sauce{32%grams}, @soy sauce{25%ml}, @water{75%ml} for the sauce and @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} along with two thirds of the @sweet chilli sauce{48%grams}.

Set the sauce aside for later. Once the veg has softened, remove the pan from the heat and set aside for later.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another large frying pan on medium-high heat. Once hot, gently add the @vegetable gyozas{1%pack} and fry until golden on the bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce the heat to medium-low, add a tbsp of @water{} to the pan and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Cook until piping hot, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove the pan from the heat, remove the lid and drizzle over the remaining sweet chilli sauce. Turn to coat the gyozas in the sauce.

Pop the pan of veg back on medium high heat. Add the @udon noodles{220%grams} and sauce to the pan. Toss to coat and simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Share your udon stir-fry between your #bowls{}. Top with the sweet chilli gyozas and sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%grams} to finish. Enjoy!

